test_if_sublist_product_equals_number:
assert 2209 == 47
 +  where 2209 = <built-in function prod>([1, 47, 1, 47])
 +    where <built-in function prod> = math.prod
test_presence_of_duplicates_in_result:
assert (3 == 3 and 99 == 3)
 +  where 3 = <built-in method count of list object at 0x7ef61d201e00>([47])
 +    where <built-in method count of list object at 0x7ef61d201e00> = [[1, 47], [1, 47, 1], [1, 47, 1, 47], [1, 47, 1, 47, 1], [1, 47, 1, 47, 1, 47], [1, 47, 1, 47, 1, 47], ...].count
 +  and   99 = <built-in method count of list object at 0x7ef61d201e00>([1, 47])
 +    where <built-in method count of list object at 0x7ef61d201e00> = [[1, 47], [1, 47, 1], [1, 47, 1, 47], [1, 47, 1, 47, 1], [1, 47, 1, 47, 1, 47], [1, 47, 1, 47, 1, 47], ...].count
